-- Areva to Appeal Exclusion From CEZ Tender, CEO Tells Hospodarske
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-10-31T07:24:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-31/areva-to-appeal-exclusion-from-cez-tender-ceo-tells-hospodarske.html
Areva SA (AREVA)  will contest its exclusion
from  CEZ AS (CEZ) ’s tender for the construction of nuclear reactors
with the Czech anti-monopoly office and European Union,
Hospodarske Noviny reported, citing an interview with Chief
Executive Officer Luc Oursel.  CEZ didn’t treat Areva on equal terms with the other two
bidders, Westinghouse Electric Corp. and a Russian-Czech
consortium led by Rosatom Corp.’s unit ZAO Atomstroyexport,
Oursel said in an interview published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  